===Etymology===
French ''absinthe'', from Latin [[Absinthium|absinthium]]

===Noun===
#The [[plant]] [[absinthium]] or common [[wormwood]].
#A strong [[spirituous]] [[liqueur]] made from wormwood and [[brandy]] or alcohol.
===Parody===
#From two Latin words, ad, and sinistrum, meaning "to the bad."  If in doubt, try one.  (Old adage, "Absinthe makes the jag last longer)." - 1904, ''[[The Foolish Dictionary]]''

